  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the provision of explanations for the evaluation process moderates the impact of the evaluator on fairness perception.",
    "Without explanations, students are more likely to perceive AI evaluations as fairer than teacher evaluations.",
    "However, when clear explanations are provided, the influence of the evaluator on fairness perception weakens, leading to no significant difference in perceived fairness between AI algorithms and teachers among college students.",
    "These findings have significant practical implications for educational institutions and policymakers.",
    "Recognizing the impact of the evaluator on fairness perception, it is imperative to ensure that both AI algorithms and teachers adhere to the principles of fairness in educational evaluation."
  ],
